From b8284e11aada24b8a61437754ae09b827aa97fc0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:27:19 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: QSDKPROTOCOL wifi Fix station association issue in 
 MHz during bandwidth change for GHz interface

When the AP changes bandwidth to 40 MHz and station try to reconfig
new bandwidth (40 MHz) based on the received beacon from AP via
ieee80211_config_bw(), the function assign bandwidth based on HT
operation, but for 6 GHz band HT and VHT operation is not supported,
due to this 6 GHz station not able to get correct bandwidth (40 MHz)
and associate with default bandwidth (20 MHz).

To address this issue, allow bandwidth configuration based on HE and
EHT operation for 6 GHz interface.

Patch-dependency: None
patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Aaradhana Sahu <quic_aarasahu@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/mac80211/mlme.c | 10 ++++++----
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/mlme.c b/net/mac80211/mlme.c
index d730d66..b9d8872 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/mlme.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/mlme.c
@@ -1164,10 +1164,12 @@ static int ieee80211_config_bw(struct ieee80211_link_data *link,
 	 * this may be applicable even if channel is identical
 	 */
 	if (elems->ht_operation) {
-		ht_opmode = le16_to_cpu(elems->ht_operation->operation_mode);
-		if (link->conf->ht_operation_mode != ht_opmode) {
-			*changed |= BSS_CHANGED_HT;
-			link->conf->ht_operation_mode = ht_opmode;
+		if (channel->band != NL80211_BAND_6GHZ) {
+			ht_opmode = le16_to_cpu(elems->ht_operation->operation_mode);
+			if (link->conf->ht_operation_mode != ht_opmode) {
+				*changed |= BSS_CHANGED_HT;
+				link->conf->ht_operation_mode = ht_opmode;
+			}
 		}
 	}
 
